  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter is concerned with the republication in the form of a volume, of Samuel Joseph May&apos;s &quot;Anti Slavery Recollections,&quot; originally printed in the Christian Register. [See Samuel J. May&apos;s Some Recollections of our Anti-Slavery Conflict.] May wants Maria Weston Chapman&apos;s help in correcting errors and making additions. May has repeatedly told his readers that he was &quot;only attempting to give sketches---not a complete history of the Anti-Slavery conflict.&quot; May requests that Maria Weston Chapman revive his recollections of Nathaniel P. Rogers. He also asks about the name of a New Hampshire lawyer &quot;who went to New Orleans to settle the estate of a deceased brother---found it insolvent---and was obliged to allow his brother&apos;s daughters and their mother to be sold as part of the assets.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
